About Us

Wellington Management offers comprehensive investment management capabilities that span nearly all segments of the global capital markets. Our investment solutions, tailored to the unique return and risk objectives of institutional clients in more than 60 countries, draw on a robust body of proprietary research and a collaborative culture that encourages independent thought and healthy debate. As a private partnership, we believe our ownership structure fosters a long-term view that aligns our perspectives with those of our clients.

About the Role

The Role

We are seeking to recruit a Global industry Analyst (GIA) to join our Industrials team within the Investment Research Group, based in Hong Kong. The GIA will most likely be responsible for researching companies related to Batteries, Building Materials and Heavy Machinery in the APAC and India region(s), aiming to generate differentiated insights by asking innovative questions, anticipating trends, and identifying risks and potential disruptions in these rapidly evolving industries. The ideal candidate should be able to communicate and implement ideas with a highly analytical and detailed approach. They will work closely with an experienced APAC & Japan Industrials GIA in Hong Kong, as well as with regional Portfolio Managers, and other GIAs globally. At Wellington, we view research as a core engine of the investment process, and consider this a career position that can be both highly challenging and rewarding, contributing to the firm's ability to generate alpha for our clients.

Responsibilities

Responsibilities for this position will include the following:

Perform continuous due diligence and stay abreast on relevant companies within a range of Industrials sub-sectors in APAC and India;

Create and maintain detailed financial models to aid in analyzing existing and prospective investments;

Attend company meetings, and industry conferences specific to areas of coverage;

Complete complex analytical projects under tight time constraints;

Maintain the integrity of industry and comparative valuation models;

Contribute to written research and investment discussions in various internal forums;

Make investment recommendations to global investment teams;

Work to identify emerging research trends' and novel and investable developments.

Essential Skills

We are seeking a self-motivated, diligent team player with a passion for the Industrials sector, and for investing in APAC markets. This role is ideal for someone with strong analytical skills, excellent financial modeling abilities, and a desire to apply their expertise to support Wellington’s Global Industry Research Team. The successful candidate will thrive in a highly collaborative investment environment, and will build strong, trusting relationships with colleagues across global teams. Effective communication skills (both verbal and written), and the ability to contribute to an open investment dialogue are essential. A growth mindset, characterized by flexibility and a willingness to continue learning, evolving, and growing as a Global Industry Analyst, is crucial. The GIA will bring a global perspective and a creative approach to analyzing investment opportunities in the region.

The ideal candidate is likely to possess the following qualifications:

An undergraduate degree with a strong academic record;

CFA (or progress towards completion) preferred;  

10+ years of relevant financial research experience, ideally including Buy side experience. Experience of covering one or more of the Batteries, Building Materials or Heavy Machinery sectors is highly preferable;

Strong financial modeling skills;

Sound judgment, strong work ethic and the highest personal and professional integrity;

Disciplined, with a strong bottom-up fundamental approach to research;

Self-awareness and resilience to be comfortable when wrong;

Ability to build relationships and collaborate with experienced, cross-functional investment teams;

Ability to work independently where needed, and to make decisions in the face of uncertainty;

Ability to organize, manage, and prioritize time well;

Strong attention to detail;

Strong communication skills, and a desire and appetite for continuous learning;                   

Fluency in English required. Fluency in Mandarin would be advantageous.

Please note that we are only able to respond to successful applicants.

Not sure you meet 100% of our qualifications?  That’s ok. If you believe that you could excel in this role, we encourage you to apply and welcome a chance to review your background. We are dedicated to building and maintaining a diversified workforce and considering a broad array of candidates with a variety of skill, workplace experiences, and backgrounds.

As an equal opportunity employer, Wellington Management ensures that all qualified applicants will receive equal consideration for employment without regard to race, color, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, religion, creed, national origin, age, ancestry, disability (physical or mental), medical condition, citizenship, marital status, pregnancy, veteran or military status, genetic information or any other characteristic protected by applicable law. If you are a candidate with a disability, or are assisting a candidate with a disability, and require an accommodation to apply for one of our jobs, please email us at GMWTalentOperations@wellington.com.

SEI Investments is a leading global provider of asset management and investment technology solutions.  The company’s innovative solutions help corporations, financial institutions, financial advisors, and affluent families create and manage wealth. SEI is a people focused organization which encourages and recognizes employee development as being a critical component in the provision of excellent client service. An open, collaborative and detail oriented environment underpins this business objective.

Whilst the parent company has its principal offices in the United States, the SEI Group comprises operating subsidiaries in the EU, UK, Cayman Islands and Canada. The SEI Group’s operations in Ireland are carried out through three entities based in Dublin that conduct the Group’s business of managing proprietary UCITS and AIF funds, as well as providing administration and depositary services to funds established by third party investment managers. 

Position Description:

The Regulatory Reporting & Financial Reporting Senior Analyst will be responsible for assisting in the preparation of various Central Bank of Ireland (“CBI”) Regulatory reports and financial statements. The CBI Regulatory reports include MMIFs, Monthly NAV return, Quarterly SPV returns and Quarterly Non-Irish Return. The Regulatory Reporting & Financial Reporting Senior Analyst will also assist the Financial Reporting team with various other functions of the Financial Reporting department.

What you’ll do:

Responsible for timely and accurate preparation of monthly and quarterly CBI Regulatory Reports and Filings.

Serve as the main point of contact with CBI, as well as subject matter expert for internal and external stakeholders.

Respond to queries and information requests from CBI within defined deadlines.

Update and maintain regulatory reporting procedure documents.

Compliance with service level agreements with the accounting teams / external stakeholders.

Assisting in the preparation of Annual, Interim and Quarterly Financial Statements.

Assisting in the coordinating, planning and completion of audits / audit requirements.

Completing Annual and Semi-Annual Filings.

Responding to queries and information requests from clients and/ or auditors within defined deadlines.

Maintaining a Central Library of All Audited Financial Statements.

Working with Financial Reporting Team members to ensure deadlines are met.

Train, coach and mentor employees on the team where appropriate.

Carry out all duties assigned to your role under the Company’s Safety Statement, to ensure Health, Safety and Well-being for all employees for whom you have responsibility.

Ad hoc tasks / projects as required.

What you bring to the table:

18 months - 2 years funds OR audit experience;

Finance related Degree or part-qualified Accountant;

Experience in preparing regulatory returns;

Knowledge of Irish/UK GAAP and International GAAP;

Account preparation experience with experience in a similar role;

P.C. literate – experience of Microsoft Office package essential;

Fluency in English Language (both verbal and written) essential;

Knowledge of the Advent Geneva system;

Knowledge of Sungard InvestOne system;

Attributes we value:

Strong oral and written communication skills – comfortable dealing with internal/external stakeholders;

Strong organizational skills;

Individual who takes initiative and ownership of assigned responsibilities;

Positive ‘can do’ attitude with excellent problem solving skills;

Detail-oriented;

Team player;

Ability to work stand alone or as part of a team;

Flexibility, adaptability and willingness to learn essential;

SEI is an Equal Opportunity Employer and so much more…

We recognize that our people are our most valuable asset and are (literally) invested in your success; we know that a healthy, happy and motivated workforce is key to our continued growth. We are focused on ensuring a healthy work-life balance and offer our employees benefits which include private medical care for you and your family, educational assistance scheme and actively encourage work life balance.

